  "title": "Who Drinks Mocktails on the Beach?!",
  "description": "Told in the style of Fleabag with an early 2000’s pop-punk soundtrack, this award-winning one-woman comedy follows party-girl Candace as she runs away to Mexico for her best friend's destination wedding. You won't have regrets... but Candace might. Awards: Outstanding Production, Audience Choice (On the Edge Fringe 2024)",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Sara Mayfield<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Damon Bradley Jang<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Sara Mayfield<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Andrew Wade<br/>",
  "website": "https://paintedfernproductions.com",
  "plain_language": "\"Who Drinks Mocktails on the Beach?!\" is a one-woman show about a girl named Candace going to her best friend Jacki's wedding in Mexico. Candace's party-girl persona is challenged as she tells the audience stories about her relationships and past experiences. As we follow her through the wedding activities, she tells us about Jacki's pet cat, a night she met a guest at a hotel, her ex-boyfriend who had a thing for feet, and how Jacki met her fiancée Ken.",
